# Re-order Logistic Model

This section describes a logistic regression–based model for predicting product re-orders for users, developed as part of the **Advanced Artificial Intelligence** module.

The system predicts the likelihood that a given user will re-order a particular product based on their historical purchasing behaviour, and outputs the top-K most likely products.

---

## Project Structure

### Data Generation

- `data_generation.py`  
  Generates a synthetic grocery dataset with realistic purchasing and reordering behaviour.  
  Outputs the CSV files listed below.

- `users.csv`  
  Contains user identifiers (200 users).

- `products.csv`  
  Contains product identifiers and product categories (150 products).

- `orders.csv`  
  Contains order-level information, including user ID and order number.

- `order_products.csv`  
  Contains product-level order data, including the binary target variable `reordered`.

---

### Model & Exported Artefacts

- `reorder_model.joblib`  
  Trained scikit-learn pipeline including preprocessing and logistic regression classifier.

- `product_purchase_counts.joblib`  
  Dictionary mapping product IDs to total purchase counts.

- `product_reorder_rates.joblib`  
  Dictionary mapping product IDs to average reorder rates.

These artefacts allow inference to be performed without retraining the model.

---

## Data Description

The data is generated synthetically based on the structure and behavioural patterns of the Instacart Online Grocery Basket Analysis dataset:

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/yasserh/instacart-online-grocery-basket-analysis-dataset

The synthetic data mirrors key characteristics of the real dataset while remaining lightweight and fully controllable for experimentation.

For full details of the data generation process, see:

